<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 22 at 2:49PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Armstrong, southern Carson and west central Donley Counties through
315 PM CDT...
At 249 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southwest of Goodnight, or 11 miles southeast of Claude, moving
northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Goodnight.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
